Freital: Windberg Festival cancelled due to Corona
The Windbergfest will not take place this year.
The city of Freital has cancelled the three-day festival planned for September.
In other years, more than 30,000 people had visited this city festival.
"We really did not make this decision easy for ourselves and - aware of how difficult it is economically for those involved - hoped until the last minute," explained Lord Mayor Uwe Rumberg (independent).
"But ultimately, as organizers, we are responsible for the health of many thousands of people".
If tens of thousands had flocked to the festival grounds and the marquee, minimum distances, hygiene regulations and contact tracking in accordance with the current Corona Protection Regulation could not have been complied with.
Or the restrictions would have been so severe that there would not have been much left of a folk festival.
Moreover, the organisational and monitoring effort would increase disproportionately many times over.
Rumberg put off for next year.
